<div id="content">

<h2><span class="title" >Getting OneTime</span></h2>

<center><a href="./" 
        ><img style="vertical-align: middle;"
              src="images/logo/onetime-logo-color-32x32.png" 
              alt="OneTime logo" /></a></center>

<p class="notice" >Please use OneTime <strong>1XVERSION</strong>
unless you want to help beta-test 2XVERSION.</p>

<div class="row">

  <div class="three column">
    <p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >GNU/Linux, Unix, Mac:</span>
      <ul style="list-style-type: circle; ">
      <li><p><a href="onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz" >onetime-2XVERSION.tar.gz</a>
          <span style="font-style: italic;" 
                >(recommended for beta testers)</span></p></li>
      <li><p><a href="onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz" >onetime-1XVERSION.tar.gz</a>
          <span style="font-style: italic;" 
                >(recommended for everyone else)</span></p></li>
      </ul></p>
  </div>

  <div class="three column">
    <p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Windows (.zip):</span>
      <ul style="list-style-type: circle; ">
      <li><p><a href="onetime-2XVERSION.zip" >onetime-2XVERSION.zip</a>
          <span style="font-style: italic;" 
                >(recommended for beta testers)</span></p></li>
      <li><p><a href="onetime-1XVERSION.zip" >onetime-1XVERSION.zip</a>
          <span style="font-style: italic;" 
                >(recommended for everyone else)</span></p></li>
      </ul></p>
  </div>

  <div class="three column">
    <p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Debian:</span></p>

    <p>OneTime 1.x is packaged in the <a href="http://debian.org/"
    >Debian</a> "testing" distribution as <tt>onetime</tt>.</p>

    <p style="font-style: italic;" >As of June 2016, the version of
    OneTime packaged in Debian is somewhat behind the upstream
    release.  We'll try to get Debian updated soon after OneTime 2.0
    comes out.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="three column">
  <p><span style="font-weight: bold;" >Standalone:</span></p>
    <p>Download the <a href="onetime-1XVERSION"
    >standalone 1XVERSION</a> or <a href="onetime"
    >standalone 2XVERSION</a> script directly, if you don't want the
    README, the test suite, or other incidental files.</p>
  </div>

</div>

<p style="text-align: center;">For access to development source code,
see the <a href="https://github.com/kfogel/OneTime" >Development page</a>.</p>

</body>
